39/******************************************************************************
40 * Raw code
41 *****************************************************************************/
42
43typedef struct {
44 int dataLength;
45 unsigned char *data;
46 int eccLength;
47 unsigned char *ecc;
48} RSblock;
49
50typedef struct {
51 int version;
52 int dataLength;
53 int eccLength;
54 unsigned char *datacode;
55 unsigned char *ecccode;
56 int b1;
57 int blocks;
58 RSblock *rsblock;
59 int count;
60} QRRawCode;
61
62static void RSblock_initBlock(RSblock *block, int dl, unsigned char *data, int el, unsigned char *ecc)
63{
64 block->dataLength = dl;
65 block->data = data;
66 block->eccLength = el;
67 block->ecc = ecc;
68
69 RSECC_encode(dl, el, data, ecc);
70}
71
72static int RSblock_init(RSblock *blocks, int spec[5], unsigned char *data, unsigned char *ecc)
73{
74 int i;
75 RSblock *block;
76 unsigned char *dp, *ep;
77 int el, dl;
78
79 dl = QRspec_rsDataCodes1(spec);
80 el = QRspec_rsEccCodes1(spec);
81
82 block = blocks;
83 dp = data;
84 ep = ecc;
85 for(i=0; i<QRspec_rsBlockNum1(spec); i++) {
86 RSblock_initBlock(block, dl, dp, el, ep);
87 dp += dl;
88 ep += el;
89 block++;
90 }
91
92 if(QRspec_rsBlockNum2(spec) == 0) return 0;
93
94 dl = QRspec_rsDataCodes2(spec);
95 el = QRspec_rsEccCodes2(spec);
96 for(i=0; i<QRspec_rsBlockNum2(spec); i++) {
97 RSblock_initBlock(block, dl, dp, el, ep);
98 dp += dl;
99 ep += el;
100 block++;
101 }
102
103 return 0;
104}
105
106__STATIC void QRraw_free(QRRawCode *raw);
107__STATIC QRRawCode *QRraw_new(QRinput *input)
108{
109 QRRawCode *raw;
110 int spec[5], ret;
111
112 raw = (QRRawCode *)malloc(sizeof(QRRawCode));
113 if(raw == NULL) return NULL;
114
115 raw->datacode = QRinput_getByteStream(input);
116 if(raw->datacode == NULL) {
117 free(raw);
118 return NULL;
119 }
120
121 QRspec_getEccSpec(input->version, input->level, spec);
122
123 raw->version = input->version;
124 raw->b1 = QRspec_rsBlockNum1(spec);
125 raw->dataLength = QRspec_rsDataLength(spec);
126 raw->eccLength = QRspec_rsEccLength(spec);
127 raw->ecccode = (unsigned char *)malloc(raw->eccLength);
128 if(raw->ecccode == NULL) {
129 free(raw->datacode);
130 free(raw);
131 return NULL;
132 }
133
134 raw->blocks = QRspec_rsBlockNum(spec);
135 raw->rsblock = (RSblock *)calloc(raw->blocks, sizeof(RSblock));
136 if(raw->rsblock == NULL) {
137 QRraw_free(raw);
138 return NULL;
139 }
140 ret = RSblock_init(raw->rsblock, spec, raw->datacode, raw->ecccode);
141 if(ret < 0) {
142 QRraw_free(raw);
143 return NULL;
144 }
145
146 raw->count = 0;
147
148 return raw;
149}
150
151/**
152 * Return a code (byte).
153 * This function can be called iteratively.
154 * @param raw raw code.
155 * @return code
156 */
157__STATIC unsigned char QRraw_getCode(QRRawCode *raw)
158{
159 int col, row;
160 unsigned char ret;
161
162 if(raw->count < raw->dataLength) {
163 row = raw->count % raw->blocks;
164 col = raw->count / raw->blocks;
165 if(col >= raw->rsblock[0].dataLength) {
166 row += raw->b1;
167 }
168 ret = raw->rsblock[row].data[col];
169 } else if(raw->count < raw->dataLength + raw->eccLength) {
170 row = (raw->count - raw->dataLength) % raw->blocks;
171 col = (raw->count - raw->dataLength) / raw->blocks;
172 ret = raw->rsblock[row].ecc[col];
173 } else {
174 return 0;
175 }
176 raw->count++;
177 return ret;
178}
179
180__STATIC void QRraw_free(QRRawCode *raw)
181{
182 if(raw != NULL) {
183 free(raw->datacode);
184 free(raw->ecccode);
185 free(raw->rsblock);
186 free(raw);
187 }
188}
189
190/******************************************************************************
191 * Raw code for Micro QR Code
192 *****************************************************************************/
193
194typedef struct {
195 int version;
196 int dataLength;
197 int eccLength;
198 unsigned char *datacode;
199 unsigned char *ecccode;
200 RSblock *rsblock;
201 int oddbits;
202 int count;
203} MQRRawCode;
204
205__STATIC void MQRraw_free(MQRRawCode *raw);
206__STATIC MQRRawCode *MQRraw_new(QRinput *input)
207{
208 MQRRawCode *raw;
209
210 raw = (MQRRawCode *)malloc(sizeof(MQRRawCode));
211 if(raw == NULL) return NULL;
212
213 raw->version = input->version;
214 raw->dataLength = MQRspec_getDataLength(input->version, input->level);
215 raw->eccLength = MQRspec_getECCLength(input->version, input->level);
216 raw->oddbits = raw->dataLength * 8 - MQRspec_getDataLengthBit(input->version, input->level);
217 raw->datacode = QRinput_getByteStream(input);
218 if(raw->datacode == NULL) {
219 free(raw);
220 return NULL;
221 }
222 raw->ecccode = (unsigned char *)malloc(raw->eccLength);
223 if(raw->ecccode == NULL) {
224 free(raw->datacode);
225 free(raw);
226 return NULL;
227 }
228
229 raw->rsblock = (RSblock *)calloc(1, sizeof(RSblock));
230 if(raw->rsblock == NULL) {
231 MQRraw_free(raw);
232 return NULL;
233 }
234
235 RSblock_initBlock(raw->rsblock, raw->dataLength, raw->datacode, raw->eccLength, raw->ecccode);
236
237 raw->count = 0;
238
239 return raw;
240}
241
242/**
243 * Return a code (byte).
244 * This function can be called iteratively.
245 * @param raw raw code.
246 * @return code
247 */
248__STATIC unsigned char MQRraw_getCode(MQRRawCode *raw)
249{
250 unsigned char ret;
251
252 if(raw->count < raw->dataLength) {
253 ret = raw->datacode[raw->count];
254 } else if(raw->count < raw->dataLength + raw->eccLength) {
255 ret = raw->ecccode[raw->count - raw->dataLength];
256 } else {
257 return 0;
258 }
259 raw->count++;
260 return ret;
261}
262
263__STATIC void MQRraw_free(MQRRawCode *raw)
264{
265 if(raw != NULL) {
266 free(raw->datacode);
267 free(raw->ecccode);
268 free(raw->rsblock);
269 free(raw);
270 }
271}

274/******************************************************************************
275 * Frame filling
276 *****************************************************************************/
277
278typedef struct {
279 int width;
280 unsigned char *frame;
281 int x, y;
282 int dir;
283 int bit;
284 int mqr;
285} FrameFiller;
286
287static void FrameFiller_set(FrameFiller *filler, int width, unsigned char *frame, int mqr)
288{
289 filler->width = width;
290 filler->frame = frame;
291 filler->x = width - 1;
292 filler->y = width - 1;
293 filler->dir = -1;
294 filler->bit = -1;
295 filler->mqr = mqr;
296}
297
298static unsigned char *FrameFiller_next(FrameFiller *filler)
299{
300 unsigned char *p;
301 int x, y, w;
302
303 if(filler->bit == -1) {
304 filler->bit = 0;
305 return filler->frame + filler->y * filler->width + filler->x;
306 }
307
308 x = filler->x;
309 y = filler->y;
310 p = filler->frame;
311 w = filler->width;
312
313 if(filler->bit == 0) {
314 x--;
315 filler->bit++;
316 } else {
317 x++;
318 y += filler->dir;
319 filler->bit--;
320 }
321
322 if(filler->dir < 0) {
323 if(y < 0) {
324 y = 0;
325 x -= 2;
326 filler->dir = 1;
327 if(!filler->mqr && x == 6) {
328 x--;
329 y = 9;
330 }
331 }
332 } else {
333 if(y == w) {
334 y = w - 1;
335 x -= 2;
336 filler->dir = -1;
337 if(!filler->mqr && x == 6) {
338 x--;
339 y -= 8;
340 }
341 }
342 }
343 if(x < 0 || y < 0) return NULL;
344
345 filler->x = x;
346 filler->y = y;
347
348 if(p[y * w + x] & 0x80) {
349 // This tail recursion could be optimized.
350 return FrameFiller_next(filler);
351 }
352 return &p[y * w + x];
353}
354
355#ifdef WITH_TESTS
356extern unsigned char *FrameFiller_test(int version)
357{
358 int width;
359 unsigned char *frame, *p;
360 int i, length;
361 FrameFiller filler;
362
363 width = QRspec_getWidth(version);
364 frame = QRspec_newFrame(version);
365 if(frame == NULL) return NULL;
366 FrameFiller_set(&filler, width, frame, 0);
367 length = QRspec_getDataLength(version, QR_ECLEVEL_L) * 8
368 + QRspec_getECCLength(version, QR_ECLEVEL_L) * 8
369 + QRspec_getRemainder(version);
370 for(i=0; i<length; i++) {
371 p = FrameFiller_next(&filler);
372 if(p == NULL) {
373 free(frame);
374 return NULL;
375 }
376 *p = (unsigned char)(i & 0x7f) | 0x80;
377 }
378 return frame;
379}

381extern unsigned char *FrameFiller_testMQR(int version)
382{
383 int width;
384 unsigned char *frame, *p;
385 int i, length;
386 FrameFiller filler;
387
388 width = MQRspec_getWidth(version);
389 frame = MQRspec_newFrame(version);
390 if(frame == NULL) return NULL;
391 FrameFiller_set(&filler, width, frame, 1);

393 + MQRspec_getECCLength(version, QR_ECLEVEL_L) * 8;

411__STATIC QRcode *QRcode_new(int version, int width, unsigned char *data)
412{
413 QRcode *qrcode;
414
415 qrcode = (QRcode *)malloc(sizeof(QRcode));
416 if(qrcode == NULL) return NULL;
417
418 qrcode->version = version;
419 qrcode->width = width;
420 qrcode->data = data;
421
422 return qrcode;
423}
424
425void QRcode_free(QRcode *qrcode)
426{
427 if(qrcode != NULL) {
428 free(qrcode->data);
429 free(qrcode);
430 }
431}
432
433__STATIC QRcode *QRcode_encodeMask(QRinput *input, int mask)
434{
435 int width, version;
436 QRRawCode *raw;
437 unsigned char *frame, *masked, *p, code, bit;
438 int i, j;
439 QRcode *qrcode = NULL;
440 FrameFiller filler;
441
442 if(input->mqr) {
443 errno = EINVAL;
444 return NULL;
445 }
446 if(input->version < 0 || input->version > QRSPEC_VERSION_MAX) {
447 errno = EINVAL;
448 return NULL;
449 }
450 if(input->level > QR_ECLEVEL_H) {
451 errno = EINVAL;
452 return NULL;
453 }
454
455 raw = QRraw_new(input);
456 if(raw == NULL) return NULL;
457
458 version = raw->version;
459 width = QRspec_getWidth(version);
460 frame = QRspec_newFrame(version);
461 if(frame == NULL) {
462 QRraw_free(raw);
463 return NULL;
464 }
465 FrameFiller_set(&filler, width, frame, 0);
466
467 /* inteleaved data and ecc codes */
468 for(i=0; i<raw->dataLength + raw->eccLength; i++) {
469 code = QRraw_getCode(raw);
470 bit = 0x80;
471 for(j=0; j<8; j++) {
472 p = FrameFiller_next(&filler);
473 if(p == NULL) goto EXIT;
474 *p = 0x02 | ((bit & code) != 0);
475 bit = bit >> 1;
476 }
477 }
478 QRraw_free(raw);
479 raw = NULL;
480 /* remainder bits */
481 j = QRspec_getRemainder(version);
482 for(i=0; i<j; i++) {
483 p = FrameFiller_next(&filler);
484 if(p == NULL) goto EXIT;
485 *p = 0x02;
486 }
487
488 /* masking */
489 if(mask == -2) { // just for debug purpose
490 masked = (unsigned char *)malloc(width * width);
491 memcpy(masked, frame, width * width);
492 } else if(mask < 0) {
493 masked = Mask_mask(width, frame, input->level);
494 } else {
495 masked = Mask_makeMask(width, frame, mask, input->level);
496 }
497 if(masked == NULL) {
498 goto EXIT;
499 }
500 qrcode = QRcode_new(version, width, masked);
501 if(qrcode == NULL) {
502 free(masked);
503 }
504
505EXIT:
506 QRraw_free(raw);
507 free(frame);
508 return qrcode;
509}
510
511__STATIC QRcode *QRcode_encodeMaskMQR(QRinput *input, int mask)
512{
513 int width, version;
514 MQRRawCode *raw;
515 unsigned char *frame, *masked, *p, code, bit;
516 int i, j;
517 QRcode *qrcode = NULL;
518 FrameFiller filler;
519
520 if(!input->mqr) {
521 errno = EINVAL;
522 return NULL;
523 }
524 if(input->version <= 0 || input->version > MQRSPEC_VERSION_MAX) {
525 errno = EINVAL;
526 return NULL;
527 }
528 if(input->level > QR_ECLEVEL_Q) {
529 errno = EINVAL;
530 return NULL;
531 }
532
533 raw = MQRraw_new(input);
534 if(raw == NULL) return NULL;
535
536 version = raw->version;
537 width = MQRspec_getWidth(version);
538 frame = MQRspec_newFrame(version);
539 if(frame == NULL) {
540 MQRraw_free(raw);
541 return NULL;
542 }
543 FrameFiller_set(&filler, width, frame, 1);
544
545 /* inteleaved data and ecc codes */
546 for(i=0; i<raw->dataLength + raw->eccLength; i++) {
547 code = MQRraw_getCode(raw);
548 if(raw->oddbits && i == raw->dataLength - 1) {
549 bit = 1 << (raw->oddbits - 1);
550 for(j=0; j<raw->oddbits; j++) {
551 p = FrameFiller_next(&filler);
552 if(p == NULL) goto EXIT;
553 *p = 0x02 | ((bit & code) != 0);
554 bit = bit >> 1;
555 }
556 } else {
557 bit = 0x80;
558 for(j=0; j<8; j++) {
559 p = FrameFiller_next(&filler);
560 if(p == NULL) goto EXIT;
561 *p = 0x02 | ((bit & code) != 0);
562 bit = bit >> 1;
563 }
564 }
565 }
566 MQRraw_free(raw);
567 raw = NULL;
568
569 /* masking */
570 if(mask < 0) {
571 masked = MMask_mask(version, frame, input->level);
572 } else {
573 masked = MMask_makeMask(version, frame, mask, input->level);
574 }
575 if(masked == NULL) {
576 goto EXIT;
577 }
578
579 qrcode = QRcode_new(version, width, masked);
580
581EXIT:
582 MQRraw_free(raw);
583 free(frame);
584 return qrcode;
585}
586
587QRcode *QRcode_encodeInput(QRinput *input)
588{
589 if(input->mqr) {
590 return QRcode_encodeMaskMQR(input, -1);
591 } else {
592 return QRcode_encodeMask(input, -1);
593 }
594}
595
596static QRcode *QRcode_encodeStringReal(const char *string, int version, QRecLevel level, int mqr, QRencodeMode hint, int casesensitive)
597{
598 QRinput *input;
599 QRcode *code;
600 int ret;
601
602 if(string == NULL) {
603 errno = EINVAL;
604 return NULL;
605 }
606 if(hint != QR_MODE_8 && hint != QR_MODE_KANJI) {
607 errno = EINVAL;
608 return NULL;
609 }
610
611 if(mqr) {
612 input = QRinput_newMQR(version, level);
613 } else {
614 input = QRinput_new2(version, level);
615 }
616 if(input == NULL) return NULL;
617
618 ret = Split_splitStringToQRinput(string, input, hint, casesensitive);
619 if(ret < 0) {
620 QRinput_free(input);
621 return NULL;
622 }
623 code = QRcode_encodeInput(input);
624 QRinput_free(input);
625
626 return code;
627}
628
629QRcode *QRcode_encodeString(const char *string, int version, QRecLevel level, QRencodeMode hint, int casesensitive)
630{
631 return QRcode_encodeStringReal(string, version, level, 0, hint, casesensitive);
632}
633
634QRcode *QRcode_encodeStringMQR(const char *string, int version, QRecLevel level, QRencodeMode hint, int casesensitive)
635{
636 return QRcode_encodeStringReal(string, version, level, 1, hint, casesensitive);
637}
638
639static QRcode *QRcode_encodeDataReal(const unsigned char *data, int length, int version, QRecLevel level, int mqr)
640{
641 QRinput *input;
642 QRcode *code;
643 int ret;
644
645 if(data == NULL || length == 0) {
646 errno = EINVAL;
647 return NULL;
648 }
649
650 if(mqr) {
651 input = QRinput_newMQR(version, level);
652 } else {
653 input = QRinput_new2(version, level);
654 }
655 if(input == NULL) return NULL;
656
657 ret = QRinput_append(input, QR_MODE_8, length, data);
658 if(ret < 0) {
659 QRinput_free(input);
660 return NULL;
661 }
662 code = QRcode_encodeInput(input);
663 QRinput_free(input);
664
665 return code;
666}
667
668QRcode *QRcode_encodeData(int size, const unsigned char *data, int version, QRecLevel level)
669{
670 return QRcode_encodeDataReal(data, size, version, level, 0);
671}

675 if(string == NULL) {
676 errno = EINVAL;
677 return NULL;

680}

682QRcode *QRcode_encodeDataMQR(int size, const unsigned char *data, int version, QRecLevel level)

697/******************************************************************************
698 * Structured QR-code encoding
699 *****************************************************************************/
700
701static QRcode_List *QRcode_List_newEntry(void)
702{
703 QRcode_List *entry;
704
705 entry = (QRcode_List *)malloc(sizeof(QRcode_List));
706 if(entry == NULL) return NULL;
707
708 entry->next = NULL;
709 entry->code = NULL;
710
711 return entry;
712}
713
714static void QRcode_List_freeEntry(QRcode_List *entry)
715{
716 if(entry != NULL) {
717 QRcode_free(entry->code);
718 free(entry);
719 }
720}
721
722void QRcode_List_free(QRcode_List *qrlist)
723{
724 QRcode_List *list = qrlist, *next;
725
726 while(list != NULL) {
727 next = list->next;
728 QRcode_List_freeEntry(list);
729 list = next;
730 }
731}
732
733int QRcode_List_size(QRcode_List *qrlist)
734{
735 QRcode_List *list = qrlist;
736 int size = 0;
737
738 while(list != NULL) {
739 size++;
740 list = list->next;
741 }
742
743 return size;
744}

760QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeInputStructured(QRinput_Struct *s)
761{
762 QRcode_List *head = NULL;
763 QRcode_List *tail = NULL;
764 QRcode_List *entry;
765 QRinput_InputList *list = s->head;
766
767 while(list != NULL) {
768 if(head == NULL) {
769 entry = QRcode_List_newEntry();
770 if(entry == NULL) goto ABORT;
771 head = entry;
772 tail = head;
773 } else {
774 entry = QRcode_List_newEntry();
775 if(entry == NULL) goto ABORT;
776 tail->next = entry;
777 tail = tail->next;
778 }
779 tail->code = QRcode_encodeInput(list->input);
780 if(tail->code == NULL) {
781 goto ABORT;
782 }
783 list = list->next;
784 }
785
786 return head;
787ABORT:
788 QRcode_List_free(head);
789 return NULL;
790}
791
792static QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeInputToStructured(QRinput *input)
793{
794 QRinput_Struct *s;
795 QRcode_List *codes;
796
797 s = QRinput_splitQRinputToStruct(input);
798 if(s == NULL) return NULL;
799
800 codes = QRcode_encodeInputStructured(s);
801 QRinput_Struct_free(s);
802
803 return codes;
804}
805
806static QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeDataStructuredReal(
807 int size, const unsigned char *data,
808 int version, QRecLevel level,
809 int eightbit, QRencodeMode hint, int casesensitive)
810{
811 QRinput *input;
812 QRcode_List *codes;
813 int ret;
814
815 if(version <= 0) {
816 errno = EINVAL;
817 return NULL;
818 }
819 if(!eightbit && (hint != QR_MODE_8 && hint != QR_MODE_KANJI)) {
820 errno = EINVAL;
821 return NULL;
822 }
823
824 input = QRinput_new2(version, level);
825 if(input == NULL) return NULL;
826
827 if(eightbit) {
828 ret = QRinput_append(input, QR_MODE_8, size, data);
829 } else {
830 ret = Split_splitStringToQRinput((char *)data, input, hint, casesensitive);
831 }
832 if(ret < 0) {
833 QRinput_free(input);
834 return NULL;
835 }
836 codes = QRcode_encodeInputToStructured(input);
837 QRinput_free(input);
838
839 return codes;
840}
841
842QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeDataStructured(int size, const unsigned char *data, int version, QRecLevel level) {
843 return QRcode_encodeDataStructuredReal(size, data, version, level, 1, QR_MODE_NUL, 0);
844}
845
846QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeString8bitStructured(const char *string, int version, QRecLevel level) {
847 if(string == NULL) {
848 errno = EINVAL;
849 return NULL;
850 }
851 return QRcode_encodeDataStructured(strlen(string), (unsigned char *)string, version, level);
852}

854QRcode_List *QRcode_encodeStringStructured(const char *string, int version, QRecLevel level, QRencodeMode hint, int casesensitive)
855{
856 if(string == NULL) {
857 errno = EINVAL;
858 return NULL;
859 }
860 return QRcode_encodeDataStructuredReal(strlen(string), (unsigned char *)string, version, level, 0, hint, casesensitive);
861}

863/******************************************************************************
864 * System utilities
865 *****************************************************************************/
866
867void QRcode_APIVersion(int *major_version, int *minor_version, int *micro_version)
868{
869 if(major_version != NULL) {
870 *major_version = MAJOR_VERSION;
871 }
872 if(minor_version != NULL) {
873 *minor_version = MINOR_VERSION;
874 }
875 if(micro_version != NULL) {
876 *micro_version = MICRO_VERSION;
877 }
878}
879
880char *QRcode_APIVersionString(void)
881{
882 return VERSION;
883}
